    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - INTRODUCTION - ENGINE COOLANT FLOW</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ENGINE COOLANT FLOW</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef435IN15">i.15</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the location of the engine coolant parts.
        </para>
        <para>Coolant flows from the radiator to the water pump and on through the engine to the engine temperature
            control thermostat.
        </para>
        <para>When the thermostat is closed, coolant runs through a bypass back to the water pump without going through
            the radiator. This provides for rapid engine warm-ups. When the coolant reaches 192&#176; F (89&#176; C) the
            thermostat starts to open and the coolant begins to flow to the radiator. The thermostat is fully open at
            212&#176; F (100&#176; C).
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Refer to Figures
                    <hotlnk document="e435_5.xml" xrefid="ef435IN07">i.7</hotlnk>,
                    <hotlnk document="e435_5.xml" xrefid="ef435IN08">i.8</hotlnk>,
                    <hotlnk document="e435_5.xml" xrefid="ef435IN11">i.11</hotlnk>
                    or
                    <hotlnk document="e435_5.xml" xrefid="ef435IN12">i.12</hotlnk>
                    in this Section for heater supply and return, coolant drain locations and coolant related sensor
                    locations.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
